MiniMart — Stage-3 database proof: run sequence

These scripts create the real schema from Archive/Development/Database in the
running kotlincrud-postgres / kotlincrud-mongodb containers, then seed and
verify a set of business scenarios grounded in BUSINESS_RULES.md. They are a
proof that the design works — not part of the four services' own codebases.

Prerequisite: `docker compose up -d postgres mongodb` from the repo root, and
both containers healthy.

Run every step below in order. Each step names the exact command. Steps 01–04
were already executed once (by me, before this became your responsibility) —
re-run them only if you're starting from a fresh/empty postgres_data or
mongo_data volume.

--- Schema (identity/orders/catalog/notifications) ---

01  postgres/00_identity_schema.sql       -> identity db
    docker exec -i kotlincrud-postgres psql -U kotlincrud -d identity -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 < postgres/00_identity_schema.sql

02  postgres/00_orders_schema.sql         -> orders db
    docker exec -i kotlincrud-postgres psql -U kotlincrud -d orders -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 < postgres/00_orders_schema.sql

03  mongo/00_catalog_schema.js            -> catalog db
    docker exec -i kotlincrud-mongodb mongosh -u kotlincrud -p kotlincrud --authenticationDatabase admin --quiet catalog < mongo/00_catalog_schema.js

04  mongo/00_notifications_schema.js      -> notifications db
    docker exec -i kotlincrud-mongodb mongosh -u kotlincrud -p kotlincrud --authenticationDatabase admin --quiet notifications < mongo/00_notifications_schema.js

